reviews.review: To me it was a lot like Return of the Jedi... it was a good movie  and worth going to see but I wouldnt stand in line for hours to go see it. Its better then Meh but not awesome.
I was 13-years-old when the original came out. 13-year-old me would have LOVED this latest installment. That's how I judge Star Wars movies.
This movie is an affront to fans. JJ Abrams should apologize.

BEST OF ALL THE STAR WARS !!!!  

I watched the very first Star Wars in the movie theater when I was young. Yes, they were interesting, but there wasnt a lot of depth to the characters or any real powerful message in the storyline until Darth Vader died. That was probably my second best Star Wars movie.  

This one had for more meaning and depth (and good acting) than any of the others. Hands-down! Everything made sense with this one.  It gives a new meaning to the term hero.  The ending was fantastic! I cant stop thinking about it.

So run - dont walk - to see this one. You wont be sorry.
This felt like a really Star Wars-y movie, but the story felt rushed and kind of out of nowhere. Still worth watching, but I wish the Skywalker saga could’ve ended on a higher note.

Эпизод более-менее хороший как фильм, но это уже совсем не похоже на привычные звёздные войны. Сходить на фильм можно, но лично я 30% фильма смеялся и это не из-за шуток, а из-за абсурда и бредовости происходящего

Tied so much together and done very well.  The visuals were amazing just what I expected to see in a Star Wars movie.  Character acting was so much better than previous movies. Can't wait to see it again
First SW movie that makes genuinely cruel, unnecessary choices that just don’t make sense. Left feeling very empty and sad from it.

I've seen some of the critical reviews, but if you remember this is the 9th movie, you would have to say no other franchise has been able to keep doing what Star Wars does. We loved the movie, complete with those moments that make you go "wow", favorite characters, surprises, and of course, debate over things you would have done differently. To me, this movie was everything you want in Star Wars, I'm glad I spent my Christmas Eve with my boys watching it - and I hope they continue to invent new. My only critical comment - I needed more AT Walkers!
